Password Generator

This is a simple Python program that generates a random password based on user-specified criteria, such as length and character set.
Installation

This program requires no external libraries or dependencies, as it uses only built-in modules. To run the program, simply download the password_generator.py file and run it using Python 3.x.
Usage

To use the password generator, run the password_generator.py file using Python 3.x. The program will prompt you to specify the length of the password and the character set to use, which can include uppercase letters, lowercase letters, digits, and special characters. Once you have entered your preferences, the program will generate a random password and print it to the console.
Customization

You can customize the password generator program to suit your needs by modifying the generate_password function in the password_generator.py file. For example, you can add more complex password generation algorithms, or integrate the program with other software applications. Additionally, you can explore ways to securely store and manage passwords, such as using encryption and password management tools.
